# Gym Tracker - Cline Rules 
 
## Project Overview 
Flutter-based fitness tracking app using SQLite, Provider state management, and clean architecture with repository pattern. 
 
## Tech Stack 
- Flutter / Dart (SDK 3.11.1) 
- SQLite via sqflite + sqflite_common_ffi (desktop) 
- Provider for state management 
- Target: Windows, macOS, Linux, Android, iOS (NOT web/Edge - deprecated) 
 
## Database Conventions 
- All dates stored as YYYY/MM/DD text format (NOT ISO 8601) 
- toMap() outputs YYYY/MM/DD format 
- fromMap() uses _parseDate() to normalise slashes to dashes 
- Database version 2 (RunTime added via ALTER TABLE) 
- DatabaseHelper uses singleton pattern 
 
## Training Style Independence 
- WEIGHT_TRAINING stores separate rows for Hypertrophy and Strength 
- getLatestWeightForExercise(exercise, [trainingStyle]) filters by style 
- Adding exercise with different style = NEW row (INSERT, never UPDATE) 
- EXERCISE_BODY_PARTS is style-independent 
 
## UI Patterns 
- Provider.of for data access (listen: false for async) 
- Lists in reverse chronological order (orderBy: Date DESC) 
- Dialogs for add/edit, PopupMenuItem for delete/modify 
- FilterChip for multi-select, ExpansionTile for grouped display 
- SingleChildScrollView for forms, error states with retry 
 
## Build Notes 
- Run flutter clean before flutter run if CMake cache errors occur 
- Web/Edge deprecated - do not add web-specific code 
- geolocator removed (blocked Windows) - do not re-add until GPS feature
- health package removed (was unused) - do not re-add until Health Connect feature
- sqflite_common_ffi_web removed (web deprecated) 
 
## Code Style 
- Use write_to_file for new files, replace_in_file for small edits 
- Use Python via execute_command when replace_in_file fails 
- Always verify with flutter analyze and flutter test 
- Keep warnings to zero (info-level lints acceptable) 
 
## Versioning 
- v0: Initial working version (current) 
- Update README.md and STATUS.md when introducing new versions 
- Version format: MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH in pubspec.yaml
